@hostname = localhost
@port = 5000 # Adjust if your port is different
@baseUrl = http://{{hostname}}:{{port}}/api/v1

# After logging in as a client, paste the token here (including "Bearer ")
@clientToken = Bearer YOUR_CLIENT_TOKEN_HERE 

# --- Workflow Variables (for testing specific campaign records) ---
@myCampaignId = 1 # Replace with an actual campaign ID belonging to the logged-in client
# --- End Workflow Variables ---

###
# ==============================================================================
# Client Campaign & Record Access Workflow
# ==============================================================================
#
# This file outlines API calls for a logged-in client to view their campaigns
# and the records associated with those campaigns.
#
# ==============================================================================

### Step 1: Client Login (to get @clientToken)
# Replace with actual client credentials that exist in your database.
# Ensure this client is associated with some campaigns for testing.
# @name loginClientUser
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/client/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testclient.new@example.com", # Replace with your test client's email
  "password": "clientPassword123"     # Replace with your test client's password
}

# After running the above, copy the full token (e.g., "Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiI...")
# from the response and paste it into the @clientToken variable at the top of this file.

###
# Step 2: Get Campaigns for the Authenticated Client
# Purpose: Client views all campaigns associated with their account.
# Requires: Valid @clientToken.
# @name clientGetMyCampaigns
GET {{baseUrl}}/client-access/my-campaigns
Authorization: {{clientToken}}

# The response will be an array of campaign objects.
# Each campaign should include details of associated radio stations.

###
# Step 3: Get Records for a Specific Campaign Belonging to the Client
# Purpose: Client views all records (from all radio stations) for one of their campaigns.
# Requires: Valid @clientToken and @myCampaignId set to a campaign ID from Step 2 response.
# @name clientGetRecordsForMyCampaign
GET {{baseUrl}}/client-access/my-campaigns/{{myCampaignId}}/records
Authorization: {{clientToken}}

# The response will be an array of record objects for the specified campaign.
# Each record should include:
# - Its own details (status, dates, validation_comment if any).
# - The name of the RadioStation that submitted it.
# - An array of its AudioFiles, where each audio file has a `url` for streaming.
#   e.g., audioFile.url might be "http://localhost:5000/uploads/audio/filename.mp3" 